title: Microstructure Information from Diffusion Imaging
text: Human brain can seen grey matter white matter. former composed cell bodies dendrites, latter composed axons glial cells. Neurons made cell body, dendrites, axon. cell body contains nucleus organelles, dendrites receive electrical signals neurons. axon long, thin projection carries signals away cell body neurons. axons surrounded myelin sheath, fatty substance insulates axons speeds transmission electrical signals. myelin sheath continuous, rather small gaps called nodes Ranvier. axons bundled together called fiber bundle. glial cells responsible maintaining homeostasis brain providing support protection axons. scale tissues (order micrometers) makes invisible naked eye. However, robust reconstruction brain microstructure key understanding brain function dysfunction. diffusion magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) comes . Water molcules constant random motion due thermal energy body made 80% water. diffusion water molecules brain restricted cell membranes myelin sheaths, faster along axons perpendicular . anisotropic diffusion can measured using diffusion MRI. Diffusion MRI non-invasive imaging technique makes magnetization protons sensitive diffusion applying -called magnetic field diffusion gradients. signal attenuation diffusion MRI used infer microstructure brain. enormous amount research done understand relationship signal attenuation microstructure brain many parametric models devised describe relationship. However, spatial resolution diffusion MRI limited voxel size, typically order millimeters, therefore containing many different tissue types. addition, depending experimental conditions (number, duration strength gradients time two consecutive gradients), MR signal might sensitive tissue types voxel. midi package meant list tissue models proposed literature provide tools simulate MR signal attenuation predicted models different experimental conditions. package used eponymous Shiny web application provides user-friendly interface package allows interactively visualize MR signal attenuation induced different tissue models design experimental conditions optimize sensitivity specific tissue parameters. title: Cylinder bundle compartment class — CylinderBundleCompartment
text: axis numeric vector length 3 unit norm specifying mean axis cylinder population. radius positive numeric value specifying mean radius cylinder population meters. diffusivity positive numeric value specifying diffusivity within cylinders m\(^2\).s\(^{-1}\). cylinder_density numeric value specifying density cylinders voxel. Must 0 1. axial_diffusivity numeric value specifying axial diffusivity space outside cylinders m\(^2\).s\(^{-1}\). provided, defaults tortuosity model reducing intrinsic diffusivity depending orientation dispersion. Defaults NULL. radial_diffusivity numeric value specifying radial diffusivity space outside cylinders m\(^2\).s\(^{-1}\). provided, defaults tortuosity model reducing axial diffusivity depending radius heterogeneity. Defaults NULL. n_cylinders integer value specifying number cylinders bundle. Defaults 1L. axis_concentration numeric value specifying concentration cylinders along mean axis. Defaults Inf. radius_sd numeric value specifying standard deviation radius cylinder population meters. Defaults 0. radial_model character string specifying radial model use. Choices "soderman", "callaghan", "stanisz", "neuman", "vangelderen". Defaults "soderman". seed integer value specifying seed random number generator. Defaults 1234.
